message.content:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he could type 9 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type 9 * 5 = 45 words.

After he broke his arm and had to use his left hand, he could only type 6 words per minute. In 5 minutes, he would be able to type 6 * 5 = 30 words.

The difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is 45 - 30 = 15 words.
